ce:section.ce:para:
The Kd
                      is an equilibrium constant and it inversely corresponds to the affinity of the PPy-GQD sensing layer in the absorption of ions [47]. Hence, the equilibrium constant was increased from 0.2253 to 0.5289 while the affinity constant (1/Kd
                     ) decreased from 4.4248 to 1.8907. Therefore, the tendency of the PPy-GQD sensing layer to adsorb arsenic ions was higher than that of mercury and lead ions.
